We are looking for an experienced data analyst with extensive experience in PostgreSQL and TimescaleDB. The ideal candidate will be able to demonstrate strong technical skills, excellent problem-solving abilities, and a deep understanding of database performance tuning and optimization.

Responsibilities:
- Design, develop, and maintain data models and databases using PostgreSQL and TimescaleDB
- Optimize database performance and query execution times
- Troubleshoot and resolve database issues and errors
- Create and maintain data pipelines to ensure data integrity and consistency
- Perform data analysis to identify patterns and trends
- Develop automated processes for data collection and reporting
- Communicate findings and recommendations to stakeholders
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather data requirements and implement solutions
- Document database designs, data flows, and processes

Qualifications:
- Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field
- Minimum of 3 years of experience working with PostgreSQL and TimescaleDB in a production environment
- Strong understanding of database design and optimization principles
- Excellent SQL and PL/pgSQL skills
- Experience with query optimization and performance tuning
- Knowledge of database monitoring tools and techniques
- Experience with data visualization and reporting tools (e.g. Tableau, Power BI)
- Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.


Skills and Expertise
SQL
PostgreSQL
PostgreSQL Programming


